  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Colombia: Promote the Implementation of Prevention Mechanisms and Participation Spaces for Ethnic Groups Victims of the Armed Conflict</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to promote measures of institutional adequacy and contribute to the appropriation of guidelines for the incorporation of the ethnic approach in the public policy of comprehensive attention and reparation to victims in Colombia. This will be done through the adoption of strategies that promote the implementation of different prevention mechanisms to communities at risk of physical or cultural extinction and the accompaniment, strengthening and promotion of spaces for self-government and participation for ethnic groups victims of the armed conflict in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
